                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5959</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Military Attaché in Japan (<persName type="from"
                            >Mcllroy</persName>) to the Adjutant General of the Army (<persName
                            type="to">Bridges</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="14" xml:id="d184fn14">Copy transmitted to the Department by the War
                        Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-23">February 23,
                            1933</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 268. Have reliable information that General Liu<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d184fn15">Gen. Liu Knei-tang.</note> and 10,000 volunteers near
                    Kailu have ceased opposition and pledged allegiance Manchukuo. Japan has begun
                    such military preparations in Bonin and Mandate Islands as she deems it
                    necessary, in the opinion of this office. On February 21st Peipiao was occupied
                    by 31st Infantry 8th Division in face of slight resistance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McIlroy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
